</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>For pet buffs, stick to haste and possibly sow and/or regen depending on what you're doing. Some people cast focus on their pets for the added hit points, but my pet never tanked for me that often, so I never bothered. Str, sta, agi etc., won't do anything for your pet.<br />
<br />
Our higher level pets can dual wield (only the level 55 and 61 pets, I believe), but they need to be given two weapons to activate this ability. The type of weapon doesn't matter (a rusty dagger will do the same as a fine steel longsword).<br />
<br />
At 34, the only advantage to giving your pet a weapon would be if the weapon had a proc. A velium weapon, for example, would add the proc damage when it went off. A gnoll hide lariat (procs stun) is another popular choice. But, at 34, you'll probably see more benefit from selling the weapons you come across and saving the cash for equipment upgrades.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><img src="http://www.magma.ca/~jmccourt/TrilSignVSmall.jpg" border="0" alt=""> <br />
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=359385&amp;resize=true>Trilian</a></div>
	
	
