	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Myth #1:  Our pets can only use weapons with "warrior" or "none" listed as a class.<br />
<br />
Truth #1:  Our pets can use any weapon that is droppable and works in that slot (can't dual-wield two primary-only weapons).<br />
<br />
Myth #2:  Only higher-level pets dual-wield.<br />
<br />
Truth #2:  All of our pets dual wield.<br />
<br />
<br />
Debunked both of these myths myself.  I've noticed that resists are a big issue with proccing weapons, because your pet will likely be much lower level than what you are fighting, unless you're fighting low blues.  The velium proc seems to only stick 10% of the time on the 50ish mobs I fight</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Xanden Ashenwolf, 56 Luminary<br />
Ainder Ashenwolf, 60 Outrider<br />
