	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />I am surprised that after 4 years there are still fairly simple things like the dual wielding issues that remain disputed <hr size="1" /></blockquote>IIRC, it was only recently that pets were given the ability to dual wield (and there is still debate as to whether this is a bug or not). So, it's not too surprising that we're still figuring out all the details.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />One thing I am not sure about is focus. It was mentioned by one of the posters above but I cant find it on my spell list. <hr size="1" /></blockquote>I was referring to our line of hp buffs (Talisman of Tnarg, Harnessing of Spirit, etc). You could cast one of these on your pet to increase his hit point total, but I wouldn't recommend it under most situations. If your pet is tanking so much that the extra hitpoints are needed, you're probably doing something wrong.<br />
<br />
BTW, /applaud the shaman community for knowing that it's dual wield, instead of the erroneous yet all-to-common duel wield</p>
	
	
	
